<TITLE> Tamim hits fastest ton </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 26 (bdnews24.com)  Tamim Iqbal completed the fastest hundred by a Bangladesh batsman and first by an opener against India after tea on the third day of the second Test at the Sher-e-Bangla National Stadium on Tuesday. Batting on 98, he brought up the milestone off 101 balls with an attempted hook shot off Zaheer Khan that went for four. He beat the previous holder Mushfiqur Rahman's 112-ball effort in the Chittagong Test. Tamim's second Test hundred featured two sixes and 13 fours. The left-hander was batting on 108 and took Bangladesh to 154-1 thanks to an unbroken 135-run second wicket stand with Junaid Siddique 
